sentences.english: I tried sushi at Penang and Tokyo.
sentences.chinese: 我曾尝试寿司，在槟城和东京。

sentences.english: Yes, We will go to Penang. It is cheaper.
sentences.chinese: 是的，我们会去槟城，因为费用比较便宜。

sentences.english: Also called the flag-raising mountain and penang topography top, altitude 830 metres.
sentences.chinese: 又称升旗山，是槟城地势最高处，海拔830米左右。

sentences.english: Lim Chor Yeow was born in 1966, in Penang, Malaysia.
sentences.chinese: 林祖耀1966年出生于马来西亚槟城。

sentences.english: It's a must-visit if you find yourself in Penang.
sentences.chinese: 如果你到了槟城，这里是一定要来的。

sentences.english: Roundtrip Economy class air ticket for Hong Kong and Penang on MH.
sentences.chinese: 马来西亚航空公司来回香港至槟城机票。

sentences.english: A 24 bit drum performance by primary school student of Wen Kai, Penang.
sentences.chinese: 由槟城文开小学学生呈献的二十四节令鼓。

sentences.english: The Penang version of this dish is craved by many including those who do not hail from the state.
sentences.chinese: 这个菜槟城版本希望许多，包括那些谁不从国家冰雹。

sentences.english: Many pilgrims make a visit to the Kek Lok Si on Penang island to pray for good luck.
sentences.chinese: 很多香客会拜访槟城岛上的极乐寺求好运气。

sentences.english: Now I am penang one college majoring in accounting.
sentences.chinese: 我现在正在槟城其中一间学院主修会计系。

sentences.english: When Hoay Eam came to live in Penang, I was just about to begin my journey abroad.
sentences.chinese: 当火炎来到槟城时，我正要出国求学。

sentences.english: Last Sunday, I bring my friend from Seremban to Penang Hill.
sentences.chinese: 上星期天，我带我从芙蓉来的朋友上槟城升旗山。

sentences.english: After breakfast depart to Penang Island.
sentences.chinese: 早餐后离开浮罗交怡前往槟城。

sentences.english: Penang has no natural resources to fight the coming economic crisis.
sentences.chinese: 槟城没有天然资源来应对这场经济危机。

sentences.english: For PENANG customer, we can MEET UP.
sentences.chinese: 槟城的买家，可以选择面交。

sentences.english: We ordered the Char Kway Teow and Penang Hokkien Prawn Mee.
sentences.chinese: 点了炒粿条和槟城福建虾面试试看。
